         <gmd:abstract>
            <gco:CharacterString>Plastic resin pellets are ubiquitous in coastal waters, derived primarily from accidental releases of pellets during transport or trans-shipment, and from their use in a number of industrial and consumer applications. The pellets absorb hydrophobic compounds such as POPs present in the surrounding seawater, with a concentration factor of up to 1,000,000 (Smeddes and others, 2009)</gco:CharacterString>
         </gmd:abstract>
